   190	    /// GIL-bound Python model, a non-reentrant native lib, an internal cache)
   191	    /// are not actually safe under concurrent calls. Serializing engine-side
   192	    /// makes the projection robust to embedders that are not truly
   193	    /// concurrency-safe, without the engine having to trust each impl. The
   194	    /// default `CandleBgeEmbedder` was shown safe under concurrent forwards
   195	    /// in the PR-9 pre-flight, so for it the guard is belt-and-suspenders.
   196	    ///
   197	    /// Throughput is ~neutral: `candle` fans every `BertModel::forward` onto a
   198	    /// single process-wide rayon pool, so two concurrent forwards merely
   199	    /// share that pool (trading per-embed latency, not aggregate work) rather
   200	    /// than getting 2x — serializing avoids some scheduler/cache thrash but is
   201	    /// not a large win. (An earlier "~13x" figure compared a debug-build
   202	    /// unserialized run against a release-build number and was withdrawn; a
   203	    /// PR-9 micro-benchmark put release embeds at ~14 ms short / ~960 ms for a
   204	    /// 512-token doc, watchdog overhead ~0.)
   205	    ///
   206	    /// Commit/IO stays parallel across workers (see `commit_gate`); this guard
   207	    /// wraps only the embed call. It is held by the worker across the watchdog
   208	    /// call and released here, so a timed-out (abandoned) embed frees it and
   209	    /// cannot stall the pool — the guard owns no data, so a panic-resumed
   210	    /// embed that poisons it is recovered via `into_inner`.
   211	    ///
   212	    /// Deliberate trade-off (codex PR-9 CONCERN-1, accepted): on the *timeout*
   213	    /// path the worker drops this guard while the abandoned detached embed
   214	    /// thread is still running lock-free, so serialization is briefly relaxed
   215	    /// until that thread finishes. This is the prescribed choice over holding
   216	    /// the guard inside the embed thread — which would let a genuinely-hung
   217	    /// embed hold it forever and deadlock the whole pool, exactly the wedge
   218	    /// ADR-0.6.0 Invariant 5 and this slice's spec forbid. Timeouts are the
   219	    /// fault path only; the embed circuit breaker (`embed_circuit_open`) bounds
   220	    /// how many such abandoned threads can accumulate. A future slice may
   221	    /// replace this hard serialize with an operator-configurable embed
   222	    /// concurrency limit (ADR-0.6.0 Invariant 4 pool-size override) for I/O-
   223	    /// or GPU-bound embedders; that knob is out of PR-9 scope.
   224	    embed_serialize: Mutex<()>,
   225	    /// PR-9 — embed circuit breaker. `consecutive_embed_timeouts` counts
   226	    /// watchdog timeouts since the last embed that actually returned (Ok or a
   227	    /// typed error); on reaching `embed_circuit_threshold` the breaker latches
   228	    /// `embed_circuit_open`, after which projection jobs fail fast WITHOUT
   229	    /// attempting an embed. This bounds the abandoned-thread leak from a
   230	    /// persistently-hung embedder: ADR-0.6.0 Invariant 5 forbids aborting a
   231	    /// running embed, so every timeout detaches one embed thread that lives
   232	    /// until it returns — left unbounded a wedged embedder would leak one per
   233	    /// job. The breaker latches for the engine session (a reopen resets it);
   234	    /// a half-open/cool-down retry is future work. `threshold == 0` disables
   235	    /// the breaker.
   236	    consecutive_embed_timeouts: AtomicU64,
   237	    embed_circuit_open: AtomicBool,
   238	    embed_circuit_threshold: AtomicU64,
   239	    /// EU-5b — streaming mean accumulator for the per-workspace mean
   240	    /// pinning lifecycle (`dev/design/embedder.md` §0.3). `Some(_)` iff
   241	    /// the identity is MC-required AND no mean has been pinned yet on
   242	    /// disk. The accumulator graduates to `None` after the at-pin
   243	    /// commit; subsequent docs feed nothing.
   244	    mean_accumulator: Mutex<Option<MeanAccumulator>>,
   245	    /// EU-5b — `MeanVecPinned` events queued by the projection-commit

